div.h2: Backward Pass: dL/dOutput -> dL/dQ, dL/dK, dL/dV

div.h3: Key Insight 1: V Gradient is Weighted
div.p: If position 5 attends 80% to position 2's value, then 80% of position 5's error flows to position 2's value embedding.

div.h3: Key Insight 2: Q/K Gradients Flow Through Attention
div.p: Q and K gradients depend on how much they affected the attention distribution.
Positions that were strongly attended to receive larger gradient signals.

div.h3: Key Insight 3: No Vanishing Through Time
div.p: Unlike RNNs where gradients flow through t -> t-1 -> t-2 -> ...,
Attention provides direct gradient paths from any position to any other position in a single backward pass.
Error signals flow directly from output to relevant input positionsno degradation through long chains of transformations.
The model learns to attend to positions that actually help the task, and those positions receive stronger updates.
All positions' gradients computed simultaneously via matrix operations fully parallelizable on GPU.
